Initial Row Type Indicator = Note Detail
Row[2] = 09/14/17 79 yo male presented to the ED with c/o progressively worsening SOB over the past 7 to 10 days.  The patient himself arrived with altered mental status and was placed on BiPAP.  His initial pH was 7.27 with pCO2 of 90.  Most of my HOPI was obtained from the patient's caregiver, Frank.  The patient uses 2.5 L of oxygen on a oxygen concentrator; however, he had to use his portable oxygen tank in the past few days as his needs were up to 4 to 5 L.  He reported increased cough with clear sputum.  No chills or fevers.  He uses albuterol nebulizer and tried treatments at home without much relief.  The patient's caregivers stated that the patient sleeps at home in a recliner; however, every night, he hallucinates.  Today, his hallucinations persisted throughout the day.  Another issue the caregiver brought up was that the patient has had persistent midepigastric discomfort.  His p.o. intake, decreased to about 300 to 400 calories per day due to the pain and severe nausea without vomiting.  The patient reportedly lost about 25 pounds over the past 1 month and a half.  initial pH was 7.27 with pCO2 of 90 with a repeated gas in about an hour after initiation of BiPAP, which showed a pH of 7.30 and pCO2 of 77.9.  CX Ray showed chronic appearing changes suggesting emphysema with biapical post-inflammatory pulmonary fibrosis.  The patient was admitted to inpatient service with a working diagnosis of acute exacerbation of COPD.
